==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Subway
<hw>Sub"way`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An
underground way or gallery; especially, a passage under a street, in
which water mains, gas mains, telegraph wires, etc., are
conducted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An underground railroad, usually having trains
powered by electricity provided by an electric line running through the
underground tunnel. It is usually confined to the center portion of
cities; -- called also <altname>tube</altname>, and in Britain,
<altname>underground</altname>. In certain other countries (as in France
or Russia) it is called the <altname>metro</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subworker</ent>⟦br⟧
